Task 1: Data Model Preparation
------------------------------------------
Import all 7 sheets into Power BI (or Excel Power Pivot).
Create relationships:
Sales_data[SalesOrderLineKey] â†’ Sales Order_data[SalesOrderLineKey]
Sales_data[SalesTerritoryKey] â†’ Sales Territory_data[SalesTerritoryKey]
Sales_data[ResellerKey] â†’ Reseller_data[ResellerKey]
Sales_data[CustomerKey] â†’ Customer_data[CustomerKey]
Sales_data[ProductKey] â†’ Product_data[ProductKey]
Sales_data[OrderDateKey] â†’ Date_data[DateKey]

Ensure one-to-many relationships (dimension â†’ fact).
ğŸ“Œ Outcome: A star schema model ready for dashboarding.

Task 2: Sales Overview Dashboard
-------------------------------------------
Objective: Show company-wide sales performance.
Steps:
Add a Card Visual â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount] â†’ Total Sales.
Add a Card Visual â†’ Sales_data[Order Quantity] â†’ Total Orders.

Add a Line Chart:
Axis â†’ Date_data[Full Date]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount]

This shows daily/monthly sales trend.

Add a Slicer â†’ Date_data[Year] and Date_data[Month] to filter.
ğŸ“Œ Outcome: Management can track overall performance and time trends.

Task 3: Product Performance Dashboard
----------------------------------------------
Objective: Identify best-selling products.
Steps:
Add a Clustered Bar Chart:

Axis â†’ Product_data[Category]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount]

Add a Matrix Table:
Rows â†’ Product_data[Subcategory]
Columns â†’ Product_data[Product]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount], Sales_data[Order Quantity]

Add a Pie Chart â†’ Sales by Product_data[Color].

ğŸ“Œ Outcome: Clear view of top products and categories driving revenue.

Task 4: Regional & Reseller Dashboard
---------------------------------------------------------
Objective: See how sales vary across territories and partners.
Steps:
Add a Map Visual:

Location â†’ Sales Territory_data[Country]
Size â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount]

Add a Clustered Column Chart:
Axis â†’ Sales Territory_data[Region]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount]

Add a Table:
Rows â†’ Reseller_data[Reseller]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount], Sales_data[Order Quantity]
Sort descending by Sales Amount.

ğŸ“Œ Outcome: Easy tracking of which regions and resellers are strong or weak.

Task 5: Customer Insights Dashboard
---------------------------------------------
Objective: Focus on customer behavior.
Steps:
Add a Table:
Rows â†’ Customer_data[Customer]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount]
Sort by Sales Amount (Top Customers).

Add a Donut Chart:
Legend â†’ Customer_data[Country-Region]
Values â†’ Sales_data[Sales Amount]

Add a Card â†’ Distinct Count of Customer_data[CustomerKey].

ğŸ“Œ Outcome: Helps understand top customers and geographic spread.

Task 6: Interactive Filtering
----------------------------------------------
Add Slicers for:
Year / Quarter (Date_data)
Product Category (Product_data)
Region (Sales Territory_data)
Reseller (Reseller_data)

This allows managers to slice dashboards quickly.
ğŸ“Œ Outcome: Fully interactive dashboard for analysis.

